===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dpkg-vendor` command is used to retrieve information related to the vendor of Debian software packages. It essentially identifies the company or organization that provides the software package.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dpkg-vendor --derives-from VENDOR` --> 🔍 Checks if the package vendor derives from a specific VENDOR.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dpkg-vendor --print-vendor
    
    🔹 Prints the name of the system vendor.

    $ dpkg-vendor --derives-from Debian
    
    🔹 Checks if the current system derives from Debian.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dpkg-vendor --print-vendor
    Debian
    
    🔹 This command shows that your operating system uses Debian.
